*Steps to Reproduce*
# Turn off Remote API (in Administration > Server Settings > Web Server > Edit Settings)
# Run following perl script to create review via REST API
{code}
#!/usr/bin/perl
use LWP ;
use HTTP::Cookies ;
use XML::Simple ;

$username = 'CRUCIBLE_USERNAME' ;
$password = 'CRUCIBLE_PASSWORD' ;

my $cookie_jar = HTTP::Cookies->new( );
$browser = new LWP::UserAgent ;
$browser->cookie_jar( $cookie_jar );
$xml = new XML::Simple ;

$resturl = 'http://localhost:8060/rest-service' ;
$login = $browser->get("$resturl/auth-v1/login?userName=$username&password=$password") ;
$logindata = $xml->XMLin($login->content) ;
$cookie_jar->set_cookie(1, 'remember', $logindata->{token} ) ;

$message = '<?xml version="1.0"?>
<createReview>
  <reviewData>
    <author>
      <userName>admin</userName>
    </author>
    <creator>
      <userName>admin</userName>
    </creator>
    <moderator>
      <userName>admin</userName>
    </moderator>
    <description>Review it.</description>
    <name>Test REST API</name>
    <projectKey>CR</projectKey>
    <allowReviewersToJoin>true</allowReviewersToJoin>
    <metricsVersion>1</metricsVersion>
  </reviewData>
  <changesets>
    <changesetData>
       <id>52</id>
    </changesetData>
    <repository>TestSVN</repository>
  </changesets>
</createReview>' ;

$create = $browser->post("$resturl/reviews-v1",
            Content_Type => 'application/xml',
            Content => $message) ;

print "~ FINISH ~","\n";
{code}
Supposedly, this should not work successfully. However, it create the review out. 

OR

# In the browser, type following URL:
{code}
http://localhost:8060/rest-service/auth-v1/login?userName=$USERNAME&password=$PASSWORD
{code}
# Run the second command
{noformat}
http://localhost:8060/rest-service/reviews-v1
{noformat}

When doing a custom filter in the review, an invalid filter parameter could lead to a possible SQL injection issue.

For example, note that the "state=Draft' " trailing with a single quote which is an invalid parameter:
{noformat}
http://localhost:8060/cru/reviews/?filter=custom&title=&project=&author=&moderator=&creator=&reviewer=&complete=any&orRoles=false&state=Draft'
{noformat}

This could lead to the attached error exception. See the attached screen shot.
